                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Cincinnati Ohio</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <date>6<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Novr 1848</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Revd Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Before I left <placeName>New York</placeName> on\n                                        my return to this<lb/> city I wrote you a few lines, under\n                                        date of <date>31<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> Augt.</date> by\n                                                  <persName>Mr. Abm.<lb/> Hart</persName> which you\n                                        have no doubt received. Since my arrival,<lb/> here I have\n                                        had no communication from <persName>Mr. Noah</persName> on\n                                        the subject<lb/> of the letter &amp;c I left with him for\n                                        The Trustees of the <placeName>Crosby\n                                        Street</placeName><lb/> Synagogue, proposing a union of the\n                                        congregations. I am writing<lb/> now urging him not to lose\n                                        sight of this object. I notice<lb/> it has been adverted to\n                                        and ably treated in the occident for last<lb/> month under\n                                        the head “Association.” It is lamentable to witness<lb/> the\n                                        apathy that prevails among us Jews while the world\n                                        around<lb/> us is <sic>intensly</sic> engaged on subjects\n                                        connected with the well-being<lb/> of the human family;\n                                        surely this torpor cannot last; the Jews<lb/> must go with\n                                        the stream or incur the charge of being less alive<lb/> to\n                                        the obligations imposed by their religion than any other\n                                        people.<lb/> The proposed union is so manifestly calculated\n                                        to produce most<lb/> important beneficial results as regard\n                                        both the temporal and<lb/> spiritual condition of our Nation\n                                        that I cannot abandon the<lb/> hope of soon seeing it\n                                        carried into effect. Should the constituted<lb/> synagogue\n                                        authorities decline acting upon the suggestion I<lb/>\n                                        contemplate proposing to form an association for the same\n                                        objects<lb/> to consist of private individuals of every\n                                        congregation, and shall<lb/> not hesitate to commence it if\n                                        only a dozen influential gentlemen<lb/> filled with zeal for\n                                        their faith and with a sincere desire to<lb/> witness its\n                                        professors taking their proper position amidst the</p>\n                              "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35m62q08/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
